CHILEAN DAYBOOK: February Economic Growth, CRU Copper Conference

-- B y   N a t h a n   C r o o k s
-- 
2011-04-05T03:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/chilean-daybook-february-economic-growth-cru-copper-conference.html
Chile ’s economy probably grew 6.3
percent in February from a year earlier, according to the median
forecast of 12 economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Chile’s central bank publishes its economic activity index for
February on its website at 7:30 a.m. New York time.
*CRU Copper Conference begins. Speakers include Mining and
Energy Minister  Laurence Golborne , Codelco Chief Executive  Diego Hernandez  and Anglo American Plc Copper Chief John MacKenzie.  ECONOMY:
*Chilean policy makers estimate annual inflation will exceed
their target by the end of the year before falling within the
range of tolerance at the end of 2012, the central bank said in
its quarterly monetary policy report. Annual inflation will
reach 4.3 percent in December, declining to 3 percent by the end
of 2012, the central bank said in yesterday’s report. The bank
targets annual inflation of 3 percent, plus or minus 1
percentage point over a 24-month horizon.  EQUITIES:
*The Ipsa index gained 0.6 percent to 4,738.81. Cia. General de
Electricidad SA increased 2.2 percent after Chief Executive
Officer Pablo Guarda told Diario Financiero that the power
company will invest $500 million in 2011. Cia. Sudamericana de
Vapores SA advanced 4.9 percent ahead of an April 8 vote on a
planned $500 million capital increase. Empresas Copec SA rose
1.7 percent after being reiterated ”buy” at Larrain Vial SA.  MARKETS:
*The peso gained 0.2 percent to a four-week high of 474.83 per
dollar from 475.85 per dollar on April 1.
*Two-year breakeven inflation rose eight basis points to 3.98
percent, the highest in two weeks. One-year breakeven inflation
increased five basis points to 4.21 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
